"[{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A powerful content editor, styled to match UasdI, and extensible to host any React component.\"}]},{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Based on Slate.JS, which is the framework to build such editors. Read more on \"},{\"data\":{\"url\":\"https://docs.slatejs.org/\"},\"type\":\"link\",\"url\":\"https://docs.slatejs.org/\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Slate.JS\"}]},{\"text\":\" documentation site.\"}]},{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"UUI RichTextEditor is built on top of Slate to bring UUI styles, add our extensions, panels to interact with, and to wrap this with convenient API.\"}]},{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"note-error\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"This \"},{\"text\":\"component\",\"uui-richTextEditor-code\":true},{\"text\":\" does't have dependencies on skin packages and uses skinManager approach to get components from your app skin. So it's required to pass \"},{\"text\":\"skinContexsdft\",\"uui-richTextEditor-code\":true},{\"text\":\" propsdf into \"},{\"data\":{\"url\":\"/documents?category=contexts&id=contextProvider&\"},\"type\":\"link\",\"url\":\"/documents?category=contexts&id=contextProvider&\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"ContextProvider\"}]},{\"text\":\". You can import skinContext object from your skin package.\\n\\nAlso it required to import css from editor package, pleasesdf add the following code into you app entry file: \\n\"},{\"text\":\"import '@epam/uui-editor/styles.css';\",\"uui-richTextEditor-code\":true}]},{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"note-warning\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Slate works with it's own JSON-based content format. That's allows it to be robust and flexible, but apps need to carefully consider that before using it.\"}]},{\"data\":{},\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"When you manipulate with server-side use \"},{\"text\":\"value.toJSON()\",\"uui-richTextEditor-code\":true},{\"text\":\" and \"},{\"text\":\"Value.from